Spencer's autobiography, Death Punch'd – Surviving Five Finger Death Punch's Metal Mayhem, was published on September 2, 2014, by HarperCollins imprint Dey St, and named a New York Times Celebrity Bestseller.
Five Finger Death Punch (2005–2018)
In 2005, Spencer and former U.P.O. bassist Zoltan Bathory formed the heavy metal band Five Finger Death Punch with vocalist Ivan Moody, bassist Matt Snell, and guitarist Caleb Bingham.
The group recorded its first album in 2006.

They signed a record deal with Firm Music and on July 10, 2007, released an EP called "Pre-Emptive Strike" from their debut album, The Way of the Fist, followed by the album's lead single, "The Bleeding".

In 2013, Five Finger Death Punch released The Wrong Side of Heaven and the Righteous Side of Hell Vol I & II.
In 2015, Got Your Six debuted at #1 on the Billboard top album charts.
Post-drumming career (2018–present)
On December 18, 2018, it was announced that Spencer had departed the band permanently.
Spencer cited his recent back surgery as his reason for leaving, saying in an interview in July 2020, "I physically reached a point where I wasn't being able to perform the way I like to perform.
In June 2019, it was announced that Jeremy Spencer has continued the band's support of first responders and was sworn in as a reserve police officer in Indiana.

On September 17, 2019, it was announced that Spencer would be acting, co-directing, writing and providing the music for the soft pornographic horror parody series Lady Killer TV, which he also created.
His sister Rachel Rockwell was an acclaimed stage director before her death in 2018.
For a fall 2018 tour with Breaking Benjamin, Spencer was replaced by Charlie Engen in order to undergo surgery on his back.
Spencer's musical influences include a lot of 1980s metal.
He is currently the frontman of Psycho Synner, a metal/gothic rock band where he performs under the name Grym Synner.
The band's second album, War Is the Answer, debuted at #7 on Billboard Top 200—staying in the Top 100 for 89 weeks and selling over 500,000 units.
The first single, Lift Me Up (with Rob Halford of Judas Priest), reached #1 on the Active Rock Chart and won the Revolver Golden Gods Award for "Song of the Year".
